---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="UTS Professional Review | Dylan Purbrick">
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-48 px-6 font-neue">
    <section class="mb-20">
        <span class="text-brand-purple font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.4em]">// Assignment Hub</span>
        <h1 class="text-7xl font-black uppercase tracking-tighter mt-4 mb-8">
            Professional <span class="text-brand-orange italic font-wayfinder lowercase">Review</span>
        </h1>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-8 border-l-4 border-brand-orange shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic leading-relaxed">
                This environment provides a consolidated view of the reflective requirements for the Professional Engineering Experience Review task. Navigate the site via the headers or portfolio grid to see practical evidence of these competencies, and use the purple banner to return here at any time.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="space-y-24">
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-brand-purple font-black uppercase text-xl mb-6 tracking-tight">Summary of Peer Feedback</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <p class="font-bold text-industrial-black uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest text-brand-orange">Collaboration Highlights</p>
                    <p>Coordinating the mechanical structure of our robotic system with Olivia, Muhaimin, and Eric required high-fidelity communication and clear ownership of task milestones.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <p class="font-bold text-industrial-black uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest text-brand-orange">Professional Strengths</p>
                    <p>Feedback consistently highlighted my ability to translate technical CAD documentation into actionable project costs—a skill directly applied in my Engineering Assistantship at Keith Engineering.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-brand-purple font-black uppercase text-xl mb-6 tracking-tight">Technical Reflection</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-sm text-gray-600 max-w-none space-y-6">
                <p>
                    My professional journey is defined by the intersection of academic rigor at UTS and practical immersion at Keith Engineering. At the core of this experience is a commitment to ethical conduct and technical accuracy.
                </p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 bg-industrial-black text-white p-8 rounded-sm">
                    <div>
                        <p class="text-brand-orange font-bold uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-2">Quality Control</p>
                        <p class="text-xs opacity-80 leading-loose">Responsible for final manufacturing drawing checks, cross-referencing CAD models against Bills of Materials (BOM) to mitigate material waste and engineering failure.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="text-brand-orange font-bold uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-2">Stakeholder Management</p>
                        <p class="text-xs opacity-80 leading-loose">Acting as the technical bridge between drafting teams and clients, translating site visit reports into accurate project quotations.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
